HEADWORD: Unleash
<hw>Un*leash"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>leash</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from a leash, or
as from a leash; to let go; to release; <as>as, to <ex>unleash</ex>
dogs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

